body:
r? @brson

(rust_highfive has picked a reviewer for you, use r? to override)

I am not quite happy about the way `rust_eh_unwind_resume` get linked.  It should have probably been a lang item, but I couldn't quite figure out how to plumb it through to `LLVMRustHookUnwindResume`...
:umbrella: The latest upstream changes (presumably #27176) made this pull request unmergeable. Please resolve the merge conflicts.
Addressed comments and rebased on top of master. r?
After going through all the nitty gritty I'm even more impressed now, very nice work @vadimcn!

Addressed review comments.

Also, now that I'm using `llvm.used` to prevent elimination of `_Unwind_Resume` hook by the optimizer, I moved hook injection earlier in trans, and was able to make `rust_eh_unwind_resume` a lang item!
:umbrella: The latest upstream changes (presumably #27309) made this pull request unmergeable. Please resolve the merge conflicts.
Looks good to me! r=me with a rebase
